41ad-838f-5fde9a9acf4f","uuid":"2a053097-6c4e-4cdc-b596-fb42247242fd","timestamp":"2026-03-31T15:01:07.579Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Quick search: I need to understand the `transactions` / `user_transactions` table in the backend. Find:\n1. The migration file that creates this table - what are the exact column names and table name?\n2. In `backend/services/backend/src/db.ts`, find the `insertUserTransaction` and `getUserTransactions` functions - what column names do they use?\n3. What are the valid values for the `event` column (or `tx_type` or whatever it's called)?\n\nLook in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/` for the migration file and `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts` for the query functions.","agentId":"a056d90f0e2ee0133","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information. Here's your summary:\n\n## Summary\n\n**1. Migration File & Table Schema**\n\nThe active migration is `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/009_transactions.sql` which creates the `transactions` table with these exact columns:\n- `id` (BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY)\n- `wallet` (TEXT NOT NULL)\n- `game` (TEXT NOT NULL)\n- `match_id` (TEXT NOT NULL)\n- `tx_type` (TEXT NOT NULL) — **this is the transaction type column**\n- `amount_lamports` (BIGINT NOT NULL)\n- `tx_sig` (TEXT NOT NULL)\n- `created_at` (TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now())\n\nNote: Migration 008 creates an older `user_transactions` table, but migration 009 drops it and replaces it with `transactions`.\n\n**2. Database Functions in db.ts**\n\nThere is no `insertUserTransaction` or `getUserTransactions` function. Instead, the active functions are:\n\n- **`insertTransaction(params)`** — inserts a single transaction at line 759\n  - Uses columns: `wallet`, `game`, `match_id`, `tx_type`, `amount_lamports`, `tx_sig`\n  \n- **`insertTransactions(params)`** — batch inserts multiple transactions at line 774\n  - Maps params property names: `matchId` → `match_id`, `txType` → `tx_type`, `amountLamports` → `amount_lamports`\n\n- **`getTransactions(wallet, cursor, limit, game)`** — retrieves transactions at line 790\n  - Filters by wallet, optionally by game\n  - Supports pagination via cursor (id-based)\n  - Returns columns as-is from the table, normalized via `normalizeTransaction()`\n\n**3. Valid tx_type Values**\n\nAt line 105 in db.ts, `TransactionType` is defined as a union type:\n```typescript\nexport type TransactionType = \"deposit\" | \"payout\" | \"refund\";\n```\n\nThe valid values are: **`\"deposit\"`**, **`\"payout\"`**, and **`\"refund\"`**"}],"totalDurationMs":24318,"totalTokens":33009,"totalToolUseCount":13,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":218,"cache_read_input_tokens":32264,"output_tokens":521,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":218},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
