s on username collision, then falls back to `user-{random8}`.\n   */\n  createPlayerProfile(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerProfile>;\n\n  /** Get a player profile by wallet address. Returns `null` if not found. */\n  getProfileByWallet(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerProfile | null>;\n\n  /**\n   * Get a player profile by public identifier.\n   * If identifier starts with `usr_`, looks up by `user_id`.\n   * Otherwise looks up by username (case-insensitive).\n   */\n  getProfileByIdentifier(identifier: string): Promise<PlayerProfile | null>;\n\n  /**\n   * Update a player's username. Validates 30-day cooldown (first edit is free).\n   * Throws on cooldown violation or UNIQUE conflict.\n   */\n  updateUsername(wallet: string, newUsername: string): Promise<PlayerProfile>;\n\n  /**\n   * Execute a function within a database transaction.\n   * All db methods called on the transactional Db share the same transaction.\n   * Rolls back on error, commits on success.\n   */\n  withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T>;\n\n  /** Gracefully close the connection pool. */\n  close(): Promise<void>;","numLines":60,"startLine":400,"totalLines":1120}}}
